Step 1: Download SQL Server
	Go to the Official Microsoft SQL Server Download Page
	https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/sql-server/sql-server-downloads

Choose the SQL Server Edition:
	Developer (Free, full-featured, for development/testing)
	Express (Free, lightweight, for small applications)
	Click "Download Now" under the edition you want.

Step 2: Install SQL Server
	Open the downloaded .exe file.
	Select "Basic Installation" (for a quick setup) or "Custom" (for advanced setup).
	Accept the license terms and click Next.
	Choose the installation location and click Install.
	Wait for the installation to complete.

Step 3: Download and Install SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS)
	Go to SSMS Download Page
		https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/ssms/download-sql-server-management-studio-ssms#download-ssms
	Click "Download SQL Server Management Studio".
	Run the downloaded SSMS-Setup-ENU.exe file.
	Follow the installation steps and restart your computer if required.

Step 4: Connect to SQL Server
	Open SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS).
	In the Server name field, enter:
	(local) or .\SQLEXPRESS (for Express edition).
	(local) or MSSQLSERVER (for Developer edition).
	Choose Windows Authentication.
	Click Connect.
